The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, July 17, 2004 				 Post-Puja date for flyover
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The Lake Gardens flyover will be ready by November, but the Bondel Gate flyover will take till March 2005, state public works department minister Amar Choudhury told the Assembly on Friday. The Mourigram flyover in Howrah should also be ready by November.																								Construction of the Rs 24-crore Lake Gardens flyover has been delayed due to problems related to the relocation of a food department godown and an information and cultural affairs department studio. The project was taken up in January 1995. The original project cost of Rs 24 crore has shot up to Rs 38 crore. 																								The Bondel Gate flyover, where work has been delayed due to problems over resettlement of slum-dwellers has rung up a project cost of Rs 36 crore from the original Rs 21 crore.																								The problem of resettling slum-dwellers will be sorted out soon. Local CPM legislator and Assembly chief whip Rabin Deb will take care of the matter,said minister Choudhury.																								Work on the Rs 18-crore Mourigram flyover project, too, has been considerably delayed because the area is congested.																								The PWD minister told the House that the problem of water-logging in some pockets of NSC Bose Road, in south Calcutta, was due to the ongoing work of Metro Railway. 																								We are in touch with the Metro authorities and are trying to find solutions, he said. 																								Expansion of Raja SC Mullick Road from Bagha Jatin to Garia cannot be carried out now for paucity of funds, the minister told the House.
